09:49.060 --> 10:02.480
Yes. You mentioned way back when we were talking about the city stories that you
got disillusioned with the plight of man and you alluded to it a couple of other

10:02.480 --> 10:11.980
times. how do you view technology and man's place in it and what man's future is
going to be with all this technology?

10:18.180 --> 10:32.700
That's a hard thing. I think that we have become octogen to technology. That
we're using technology to dehumanize ourselves.

10:35.320 --> 10:43.060
I understand and admit that we must have higher and ever higher technology

10:45.520 --> 10:50.080
to make ourselves to make possible a better life.

10:52.960 --> 11:13.320
After all medical technology has saved many lives. I can remember the time when
people were sick with chicken pox, dipteria were terrestre and were diseases that made

11:13.320 --> 11:24.840
everyone cringe. I can remember the polio epidemic that we had every summer. we
still have heart disease and we have cancer but one of these things we're going

11:24.840 --> 11:31.340
to look at. We have a make wage and communication.

11:34.540 --> 11:51.820
we now can listen to stars thousands of light years distance millions of light
years distance. We have gone out to most of the planets in the solar

11:51.820 --> 12:07.560
system and in a few years one of our unmaned boats would be going out and
entering space beyond the solar system. All of this is fine and it's necessary

12:08.900 --> 12:29.580
but I do have a feeling that we are being overwhelmed by technology. I am
considerably uncomfortable with the electronics that we're getting to computers.

12:30.820 --> 12:41.700
I can see the day when we will abolish money and that we will do all our
business by computers.

12:46.300 --> 12:58.400
it's going to hurt us. It's going to hurt us in the end. And still you can't
stop technology because of those things. You can see it and I'm confused.

13:01.840 --> 13:10.920
I don't think you're the only one. You are one of the few who will admit it but
I don't think you're the only one. We're back off from being so heavy now.

13:11.700 --> 13:17.540
Looking back on your body of works what are some of your favorite works that
you've done?

13:21.760 --> 13:38.360
Most people if you ask what my favorite work was would say City. And I'm pleased
that most people would say that. But I think that I have written better works

13:38.360 --> 13:58.140
than city. I think that Way Station choice of thought maybe Project Hope are
among my better works. The Visitors was a good story.

14:00.740 --> 14:14.840
It's hard to say which work you think is best. Even after some years after I've
written I'm still puzzled by which piece of work I do think is my best ever.

14:17.880 --> 14:20.540
How do you want to be remembered as a writer?

14:25.800 --> 14:44.420
I don't know if I will be remembered. But if I'm to be remembered as a writer
I'd like to be remembered as someone who wrote honestly and who is more

14:44.420 --> 14:50.860
concerned with the heart and mind of humanity than humanity's achievements.

